- Profiling is possible if enabling the COMPUTE_PROFILE variable.
- For MPI profiling, a wrapper script has to be used (like the ones in this
  directory, starting from profile.sh).
- No overhead was observed when profiling OpenCL over MPI on Daint.
- For more examples, check:
    https://bluewaters.ncsa.illinois.edu/openacc-and-cuda-profiling
- A complete reference of the available counters may be found at:
    http://www.cs.cmu.edu/afs/cs/academic/class/15668-s11/www/cuda-doc/Compute_Profiler.txt
